<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEEFF3B9BFEF7F8C3FD91F8E6" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[306,596,1805,1831]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Thoracodelphys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="430" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longiseta" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEFF3B9BFEF7F8C3FD91F8E6" box="[306,596,1805,1831]" italics="true" pageId="430" pageNumber="431">Thoracodelphys longiseta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEFF3B9BFD9FF8C0FD76F8E9" bold="true" box="[602,691,1806,1832]" pageId="430" pageNumber="431">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4EEFF3B9BFD9FF8C0FD76F8E9" box="[602,691,1806,1832]" pageId="430" pageNumber="431" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, female. A, maxilla; B, maxilliped; C, leg 1; D, leg 2; E, leg 4; F, leg 5. Scale bars: A, B, F, 0.02 mm; C–E, 0.05 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEEFF3B9AFC9AF876FDD6FE52" blockId="430.[810,1452,1942,2070]" lastBlockId="431.[136,778,173,1730]" lastPageId="431" lastPageNumber="432" pageId="430" pageNumber="431">
Leg 1 (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EEFF3B9BFC78F876FBF3F813" box="[957,1078,1975,2002]" captionStart="FIGURE 295" captionStartId="445.[136,245,1533,1559]" captionTargetBox="[170,1428,246,1474]" captionTargetId="figure-260@445.[136,1451,221,1499]" captionTargetPageId="445" captionText="FIGURE 295. Bysone bidens sp. nov., female. A, maxilliped; B, leg 1; C, leg 2; D, leg 4; E, leg 5. Scale bars: A, E, 0.02 mm; B–D, 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591885" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591885/files/figure.png" pageId="430" pageNumber="431">Fig. 295B</figureCitation>
) with 2-segmented rami; inner coxal seta pinnate; outer seta on basis small as in legs 2– 4. First exopodal segment lacking inner seta; compound 77×102, and 65×84 μm, respectively. Anal somite with deep posteromedian incision. Caudal ramus (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EEFE3B9AFD48FF01FCC4FF28" box="[653,769,207,233]" captionStart="FIGURE 284" captionStartId="429.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[256,1350,223,1845]" captionTargetId="figure-19@429.[200,1388,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="429" captionText="FIGURE 284. Thoracodelphys longiseta sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, urosome, ventral; C, left caudal ramus, ventral; D, rostrum; E, antennule; F, antenna; G, labrum; H, mandible; I, paragnath; J, maxillule. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, D, 0.1 mm; C, E–G, I, J, 0.02 mm; H, 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591859" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591859/files/figure.png" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">Fig. 284C</figureCitation>
) 4.3 times longer than wide (86×20 μm): armed with 6 setae (1 proximal, 1 subdistal, and 4 distal); proximal and subdistal setae located at 30 and 76% of ramus length, respectively; 3 of 4 distal setae bluntly tipped; all setae longer than width of ramus at base.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEEFE3B9AFF78FE55FD2CFC8F" blockId="431.[136,778,173,1730]" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">
Rostrum (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EEFE3B9AFEF5FE55FE63FE74" box="[304,422,411,437]" captionStart="FIGURE 284" captionStartId="429.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[256,1350,223,1845]" captionTargetId="figure-19@429.[200,1388,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="429" captionText="FIGURE 284. Thoracodelphys longiseta sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, urosome, ventral; C, left caudal ramus, ventral; D, rostrum; E, antennule; F, antenna; G, labrum; H, mandible; I, paragnath; J, maxillule. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, D, 0.1 mm; C, E–G, I, J, 0.02 mm; H, 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591859" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591859/files/figure.png" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">Fig. 284D</figureCitation>
) short, muchwiderthanlong, stronglytapering distally. Antennule (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EEFE3B9AFDEAFE73FD65FE16" box="[559,672,445,471]" captionStart="FIGURE 284" captionStartId="429.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[256,1350,223,1845]" captionTargetId="figure-19@429.[200,1388,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="429" captionText="FIGURE 284. Thoracodelphys longiseta sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, urosome, ventral; C, left caudal ramus, ventral; D, rostrum; E, antennule; F, antenna; G, labrum; H, mandible; I, paragnath; J, maxillule. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, D, 0.1 mm; C, E–G, I, J, 0.02 mm; H, 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591859" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591859/files/figure.png" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">Fig. 284E</figureCitation>
) 151 μm long, 7-segmented; armatureformula 3, 16, 4, 2+aesthetasc, 3, 1+aesthetasc, and 11+aesthetasc; setae crowded, all naked; 2 larger setae on first segment extremely long (about 1.5 times longer than entire antennule).Antenna (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EEFE3B9AFD52FD8BFCC6FD9E" box="[663,771,581,607]" captionStart="FIGURE 284" captionStartId="429.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[256,1350,223,1845]" captionTargetId="figure-19@429.[200,1388,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="429" captionText="FIGURE 284. Thoracodelphys longiseta sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, urosome, ventral; C, left caudal ramus, ventral; D, rostrum; E, antennule; F, antenna; G, labrum; H, mandible; I, paragnath; J, maxillule. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, D, 0.1 mm; C, E–G, I, J, 0.02 mm; H, 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591859" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591859/files/figure.png" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">Fig. 284F</figureCitation>
) 4-segmented; short coxa unarmed; basis and first endopodal segment also unarmed, both 45×28 μm; compound distal endopodal segment about 3.1 times longer than wide (59×19 μm): armed with 9 setae arranged as 4, 2, and 3 (1 of 4 proximal setae elongate, longer than segment; longest of 3 distal setae more than twice as long as terminal claw); terminal claw small, about 0.4 times as long as segment.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEEFE3B9AFF78FC9BFD23FA73" blockId="431.[136,778,173,1730]" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">
Labrum (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EEFE3B9AFEF2FC9BFE78FCB1" box="[311,445,853,880]" captionStart="FIGURE 285" captionStartId="430.[136,245,1805,1831]" captionTargetBox="[199,1404,234,1764]" captionTargetId="figure-20@430.[136,1451,187,1768]" captionTargetPageId="430" captionText="FIGURE 285. Thoracodelphys longiseta sp. nov., female. A, maxilla; B, maxilliped; C, leg 1; D, leg 2; E, leg 4; F, leg 5. Scale bars: A, B, F, 0.02 mm; C–E, 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591861" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591861/files/figure.png" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">Fig. 285G</figureCitation>
) with large, semicircular posteromedian lobeand narrow, setulose posterior margin. Mandible (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EEFE3B9AFEC3FC57FEBBFC72" box="[262,382,921,947]" captionStart="FIGURE 284" captionStartId="429.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[256,1350,223,1845]" captionTargetId="figure-19@429.[200,1388,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="429" captionText="FIGURE 284. Thoracodelphys longiseta sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, urosome, ventral; C, left caudal ramus, ventral; D, rostrum; E, antennule; F, antenna; G, labrum; H, mandible; I, paragnath; J, maxillule. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, D, 0.1 mm; C, E–G, I, J, 0.02 mm; H, 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591859" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591859/files/figure.png" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">Fig. 284H</figureCitation>
) with 5 pointed teethand 1 small seta on coxal gnathobase: basis with 1 setaon medial margin; exopod 2-segmented with 3 setae on first segment and 2 setae on small second segment, 2 proximal setae about twice as long as distal 3: endopod 2-segmented, incompletely articulated from basis; first segment armed with 2 setae; second segment much narrower than first, with 5 setae. Paragnath (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EEFE3B9AFE51FB49FE39FB60" box="[404,508,1159,1185]" captionStart="FIGURE 284" captionStartId="429.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[256,1350,223,1845]" captionTargetId="figure-19@429.[200,1388,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="429" captionText="FIGURE 284. Thoracodelphys longiseta sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, urosome, ventral; C, left caudal ramus, ventral; D, rostrum; E, antennule; F, antenna; G, labrum; H, mandible; I, paragnath; J, maxillule. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, D, 0.1 mm; C, E–G, I, J, 0.02 mm; H, 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591859" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591859/files/figure.png" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">Fig. 284I</figureCitation>
) with prominent lobe on subdistal outer margin, and denselysetulose along medial margin. Maxillule (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EEFE3B9AFEA0FB05FE16FB24" box="[357,467,1227,1253]" captionStart="FIGURE 284" captionStartId="429.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[256,1350,223,1845]" captionTargetId="figure-19@429.[200,1388,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="429" captionText="FIGURE 284. Thoracodelphys longiseta sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, urosome, ventral; C, left caudal ramus, ventral; D, rostrum; E, antennule; F, antenna; G, labrum; H, mandible; I, paragnath; J, maxillule. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, D, 0.1 mm; C, E–G, I, J, 0.02 mm; H, 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591859" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591859/files/figure.png" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">Fig. 284J</figureCitation>
) armed asin 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEEFE3B9AFDB7FB02FCCFFB24" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[626,778,1227,1254]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Thoracodelphys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="431" pageNumber="432" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadriseta" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEFE3B9AFDB7FB02FD47FB24" box="[626,642,1228,1253]" italics="true" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEFE3B9AFD57FB05FCCFFB24" box="[658,778,1227,1253]" italics="true" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">quadriseta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4EEFE3B9AFF4DFB23FF20FAC9" box="[136,229,1261,1288]" pageId="431" pageNumber="432" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEFE3B9AFF4DFB23FF25FAC6" bold="true" box="[136,224,1261,1287]" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, but seta on coxal endite shorter. Maxilla (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EEFE3B9AFD19FB23FF0DFAEB" captionStart="FIGURE 285" captionStartId="430.[136,245,1805,1831]" captionTargetBox="[199,1404,234,1764]" captionTargetId="figure-20@430.[136,1451,187,1768]" captionTargetPageId="430" captionText="FIGURE 285. Thoracodelphys longiseta sp. nov., female. A, maxilla; B, maxilliped; C, leg 1; D, leg 2; E, leg 4; F, leg 5. Scale bars: A, B, F, 0.02 mm; C–E, 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591861" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591861/files/figure.png" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">Fig. 285A</figureCitation>
) 5-segmented; syncoxawith 9 (3, 1, 2, and 3) setae; basis with 3 setae, distal seta slightly more than half length of middle seta; endopodwith 1, 1, and 3 setaeonfirst to third segments, respectively. Maxilliped (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EEFE3B9AFD4EFABBFCC7FA51" box="[651,770,1397,1424]" captionStart="FIGURE 285" captionStartId="430.[136,245,1805,1831]" captionTargetBox="[199,1404,234,1764]" captionTargetId="figure-20@430.[136,1451,187,1768]" captionTargetPageId="430" captionText="FIGURE 285. Thoracodelphys longiseta sp. nov., female. A, maxilla; B, maxilliped; C, leg 1; D, leg 2; E, leg 4; F, leg 5. Scale bars: A, B, F, 0.02 mm; C–E, 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591861" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591861/files/figure.png" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">Fig. 285B</figureCitation>
) unsegmented with 8 medial and 1 outer subdistal seta.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEEFE3B9AFF78FA74FD07F900" blockId="431.[136,778,173,1730]" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">
Legs 1–4with 3-segmentedexopods and 2-segmented endopods (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EEFE3B9AFEC2FA15FEAEFA37" box="[263,363,1499,1526]" captionStart="FIGURE 285" captionStartId="430.[136,245,1805,1831]" captionTargetBox="[199,1404,234,1764]" captionTargetId="figure-20@430.[136,1451,187,1768]" captionTargetPageId="430" captionText="FIGURE 285. Thoracodelphys longiseta sp. nov., female. A, maxilla; B, maxilliped; C, leg 1; D, leg 2; E, leg 4; F, leg 5. Scale bars: A, B, F, 0.02 mm; C–E, 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591861" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591861/files/figure.png" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">Fig. 285</figureCitation>
C-E); innercoxalsetaabsent; outer seta on basis small. Inner distal spine on basis of leg 1 not extending to distal border of first endopodal segment, 22 μm long. Second exopodal segment of leg 1 with large, tapering anterodistal process. First and second exopodal segments of legs 2–4 each with bifurcate anterodistal process. Armature formula for legs 1–4 as follows:
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEEFE3B9AFED5F922FD36F8AD" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">
<table id="F96DC47DEEFEC5CAFF4DF925FD33F8AD" box="[136,758,1771,1900]" gridcols="5" gridrows="4" inLine="true" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">
<tr id="355D349FEEFEC5CAFF4DF925FD33F8C7" box="[136,758,1771,1798]" gridrow="0" pageId="431" pageNumber="432" rowspan-0="1">
<th id="768C5DE3EEFEC5CAFED5F925FE8FF8C7" box="[272,330,1771,1798]" gridcol="1" gridrow="0" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">Coxa</th>
<th id="768C5DE3EEFEC5CAFE99F925FE5FF8C7" box="[348,410,1771,1798]" gridcol="2" gridrow="0" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">Basis</th>
<th id="768C5DE3EEFEC5CAFE6BF925FD9CF8C7" box="[430,601,1771,1798]" gridcol="3" gridrow="0" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">Exopod</th>
<th id="768C5DE3EEFEC5CAFDB9F925FD33F8C7" box="[636,758,1771,1798]" gridcol="4" gridrow="0" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">Endopod</th>
</tr>
<tr id="355D349FEEFEC5CAFF4DF8C0FD33F8E9" box="[136,758,1806,1832]" gridrow="1" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">
<th id="768C5DE3EEFEC5CAFF4DF8C0FEC6F8E9" box="[136,259,1806,1832]" gridcol="0" gridrow="1" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">Leg 1</th>
<td id="768C5DE3EEFEC5CAFED5F8C0FE8FF8E9" box="[272,330,1806,1832]" gridcol="1" gridrow="1" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">0-0</td>
<td id="768C5DE3EEFEC5CAFE99F8C0FE5FF8E9" box="[348,410,1806,1832]" gridcol="2" gridrow="1" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">1-I</td>
<td id="768C5DE3EEFEC5CAFE6BF8C0FD9CF8E9" box="[430,601,1806,1832]" gridcol="3" gridrow="1" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">I-1; 1-1; 3, 1, 4</td>
<td id="768C5DE3EEFEC5CAFDB9F8C0FD33F8E9" box="[636,758,1806,1832]" gridcol="4" gridrow="1" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">0-0; 1, 2, 3</td>
</tr>
<tr id="355D349FEEFEC5CAFF4DF8E1FD33F88B" box="[136,758,1839,1866]" gridrow="2" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">
<th id="768C5DE3EEFEC5CAFF4DF8E1FEC6F88B" box="[136,259,1839,1866]" gridcol="0" gridrow="2" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">
Legs 2 &amp; 
<td id="768C5DE3EEFEC5CAFED5F8E1FE8FF88B" box="[272,330,1839,1866]" gridcol="1" gridrow="2" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">30-0</td>
</th>
