<paragraph id="8BD236DDEEFE3B9AFF78F858FE86F7D7" blockId="431.[136,778,1941,2070]" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">
Leg 5 (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EEFE3B9AFED7F858FE44F871" box="[274,385,1941,1968]" captionStart="FIGURE 285" captionStartId="430.[136,245,1805,1831]" captionTargetBox="[199,1404,234,1764]" captionTargetId="figure-20@430.[136,1451,187,1768]" captionTargetPageId="430" captionText="FIGURE 285. Thoracodelphys longiseta sp. nov., female. A, maxilla; B, maxilliped; C, leg 1; D, leg 2; E, leg 4; F, leg 5. Scale bars: A, B, F, 0.02 mm; C–E, 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591861" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591861/files/figure.png" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">Fig. 285F</figureCitation>
) consisting of very short protopod bearing 1 seta and small, tapering free exopodal segment, 12×15 μm, armed distally with 2 setae, inner 21 μm long and outer 34 μm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEEFE3B9AFC9AFF63FBE5FF06" blockId="431.[810,1452,173,437]" box="[863,1056,173,199]" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEFE3B9AFC9AFF63FC59FF06" bold="true" box="[863,924,173,199]" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">Male</emphasis>
. Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3776556EEFE3B9AFC9AFF01FB0AFE74" pageId="431" pageNumber="432" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEEFE3B9AFC9AFF01FB0AFE74" blockId="431.[810,1452,173,437]" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEFE3B9AFC9AFF01FC09FF28" bold="true" box="[863,972,207,233]" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">Remarks</emphasis>
. The two extremely long setae on the first antennulary segment and the large anterodistal process on the second exopodal segment of leg 1 serve to characterise 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEEFE3B9AFCEFFEF8FC6EFE8E" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[810,939,309,335]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Thoracodelphys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="431" pageNumber="432" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longiseta" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEFE3B9AFCEFFEF8FC6EFE8E" box="[810,939,309,335]" italics="true" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">T. longiseta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4EEFE3B9AFC75FEFBFBCFFE8E" box="[944,1034,309,335]" pageId="431" pageNumber="432" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEFE3B9AFC75FEFBFBC1FE8E" bold="true" box="[944,1028,309,335]" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
The possession of 9 setae on the third exopodal segment of leg 3 is also an exceptional feature because this segment bears a maximum of 8 setae in all the other known species of the genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
